    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. you mentioned the coal jobs thing, but it sounds like you're saying the solar part is a \"clear benefit\" and \"pro-growth\" while the coal side is just folks \"fearing\" things. isn't the impact on coal towns a pretty huge deal though? it's not just about fear, it's about people actually losing their livelihoods. do you think the bill is actually fair to those communities?",
