      "content": "i mean, i get the retraining part, but isn't it kind of a losing battle? it feels like the bill is basically saying that the old ways don't matter anymore and we just have to move on regardless of what happens to the people in those towns. if the outcome is basically inevitable, isn't supporting this bill just a way of saying that the coal industry is dead and gone anyway?",
